  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Study will look at baseline Vitamin D levels, calcium, albumin, liver enzymes, testosterone,
      osteocalcin, urine N telopeptides, bone mineral density, nutritional assessment and physical
      activity assessment of boys with hemophilia A or B (ages 2-20 yrs). Patients with low vitamin
      D levels will receive therapeutic doses of Vitamin D. At end of one year follow up studies
      will be repeated.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
